File: All elite soccer matches in England, including the Premier League are suspended due to the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG -Â All elite soccer matches in England, including the Premier League, were suspended until April 4 on Friday due to the coronavirus pandemic, English soccer's governing bodies said in a joint statement. "Following a meeting of shareholders today, it was unanimously decided to suspend the Premier League with the intention of returning on April 4," the Premier League, FA, EFL and WSL said in a joint statement.